      "activityCount": 1,
      "description": "Frostbrand of Titania This elegant, icy blade glistens with a frost that never melts, exuding an aura of fey majesty. The blade reflects Titania’s cold beauty and dominion over the winter. The hilt is adorned with intricate carvings of snowflakes and frozen blossoms, pulsating with a faint, otherworldly blue light.\nDivine Smite (Cold): When used to perform a Divine Smite, the Frostbrand deals cold damage instead of necrotic. Upon striking, shards of ice explode from the blade, chilling the target to the bone and leaving an ethereal frost lingering in the air.\nFey Winter's Grace: On a natural 20, the blade does not simply heal—it envelops the wielder in a burst of frosty energy, restoring 15 HP and coating them in protective ice that grants temporary resistance to cold damage until the end of their next turn. This healing power is a manifestation of Titania’s favor, drawing strength from her eternal winter.\nVeldora’s Stolen Power\nOnce per long rest, as an Action:\nYou unleash a devastating bolt of lightning in a 100-foot line that is 5 feet wide, emanating from you in a direction you choose.\nEach creature in the line must make a Dexterity saving throw (DC 17) .\nA creature takes 10d6 lightning damage on a failed save, or half as much on a success.\nAfter resolving the damage, you instantly teleport to the far end of the lightning bolt’s line , appearing in an unoccupied space of your choice nearest to that endpoint.",
      "descriptionLength": 1435,
      "source": {
        "custom": "SRD 5.1",
        "revision": 1,
        "rules": "2014"
      },
